name: Angela Duby
text: Love their stuffed crust! It is pretty much two pizzas on top of each other. The stuffed crust pizza's are around $18 each, but they are worth it! Most times, one slice will fill me up while I can eat 4-5 slices before filling up of Little Caesars pizza.

name: Art Harrington
text: Came here for the first time a few weeks ago and love the pizza. I walked out with two pizzas. I have a Camp Chef Smoker and cooked my pizza in it. I was very impressed with the results, especially how well a smoker can cook a pizza. I may …More

name: Cliff Martinet
text: Great pizza. Gourmet veggie is fantastic and I say that as a meat lover. Really surprising how good take and bake can be. Our oven bakes them on the fast side so keep an eye on it!

name: Christopher Schlacta
text: I was shocked and pleased to find a Papa Murphy's still operating in the area, as I've been craving a proper Brokeback Pizza (A cowboy, covered in creamy white sauce), but I called them up today to confirm it was real and I got the tritone "The number you're trying to reach is no longer in service" :(

name: Nissim Menashe
text: First time ordering! A very unique way of buying pizza. They make it to your specific way, you take it home to bake. This is going to be a new norm. The difference between frozen and fresh! Fresh tastes so much better! You gotta try it!

name: Brian Solbrig
text: I am a huge fan of Papa Murphy's. Their pizza is bomb as hell and the cookie dough is delicious. I've never been to a "bad" Papa Murphy's, but this location is exceptional. The staff is courteous and friendly and the owner is awesome. I definitely recommend checking this place out. You won't regret it!

name: Allison Dockstader
text: It is no longer there! I'm really disappointed that Google did not remove this. Also very disappointed that Papa Murphy's didn't update their website saying this location closed!

name: Murphy Williams
text: Papa Murphy's only offers take and bake at home pizza. It's best to order online. Seems like better deals then walk in ordering. The website is easy to use.  My favorite is the Chicken Garlic pizza. Not a fan of their traditional red sauce. They have prepared salads which are good for quick lunch. Take and bake desserts too.

name: Hanspal Kahlon
text: I tried it for first time and it turned out to be good no complaints.

name: ocrascal 2014
text: Excellent pizza, superb price, and outstanding customer service. My family has been eating Papa Murphy's pizza for more than 15 years since being first introduced to the restaurant while living in Colorado Springs. Awesome food and glad they are in Southern California now.

name: Matthew R
text: Amazing in everyway! Order online, pick up at a time that is convenient. Bring coupons and save a few bucks off the order, and complete a phone survey for some yummy cookie dough! Gosh, the price is right for the high quality pizza you get! Heat that oven to 425 because it's about to get delicious!

name: N E
text: Was in the neighborhood.  Thought I would stop for awesome papa murphys pizza...  However, it looks like they shutdown this location.

name: Rachel DelReal
text: I went to the one in Napa and really liked they’re pizza. Wish there was one close by in Laguna Hills, I recommend it. I first found out about this pizza in Minnesota & liked it because you can bring it home & cook it yourself & it’s inexpensive!!!

name: Interpreter - Debbie King
text: Fast, friendly service, great toppings choices and a top notch option for a quick dinner.  Easy to follow instructions and easy clean up as well. Love this place!

name: Ashok J
text: Interesting concept of building your choice of pizza. The best part is you bake at home and consume it hot and fresh

name: LeeAnn Marsh
text: Great, fresh ingredients that I can bake when I'm ready. Friendly helpful crew.

name: daner40
text: Love this place but it is closing this week forever. I guess putting a pizza in the oven is too much work for people.

name: girlsina rv
text: I love this pizza, just so sad that this location is CLOSED!

name: Susan Peeks
text: Excellent pizza! Great owner! Glad we finally got to enjoy the fuss!!

name: Luke Hesher
text: This place was awesome, but they have closed permanently.

name: Toshi S
text: Great pizzas that you bake at home. Good ingredients and crust. Always quick in and out.

name: Ryan E
text: Excellent service. The employees made my night.. actually, they made my weekend! Thank you!

name: Rose London
text: Nice people! Great pizza!!!

name: Robert Keller
text: Best pizza. Hot out of the oven.

name: Edwin Fountaine Jr.
text: Excellent food at a great price. It doesn't get fresher than "Right out of your Oven".

name: Marina LaFountaine
text: drove to the location, couldn’t find it, called, number disconnected, called another location, this location is closed! just a heads up for everyone !

name: Mitzh Consla
text: I'm in and out in no time. Toppings are always in abundance. Service is topnotch.

name: David Schroeder
text: You can order at the store, call in an order for pickup, or order on-line. Look for specials and find your favorite signature bake-at-home pizza. We like the family size Cowboy pizza and you can get a salad for the person who does not want to eat pizza.

name: Robyn Nixon
text: Great take and bake pizza and almost always a sale on one variety or another. Such a deal.

name: ryan dehaan
text: It's the best value you can get.

name: Melanie Vance - Ryan
text:
Friendly, quick service with $10 large size special!
Yummo! :-)

name: Jaclyn Rachelle
text: Papa Murphy's isn't as popular as it deserves to be! The pizza is so great.

name: H Wing
text: The best take and bake pizza period. I hope that they open more stores around O.C.

name: A P
text: Best crust! Fast service and great pizza.

name: Brandice Strotman
text: Cheap delicious pizzas

name: Nick Caruso
text: Great but prices could be better

name: Sophia P
text: Great pizza, I love the idea of the take and bake. Plus $10 Tuesdays!

name: Alex Leszczynski
text: The staff is very nice and helpful.

name: PHER
text: Sooooo much toppings...

name: Saurabh Karnik
text: No longer exists

name: Christine Wellington
text: Always quick and yummy

name: Hannover Fisst
text: Good pizza

name: Max Gutierrez
text: Quick, easy, delicious!

name: Daniel Skadal
text: Best pizza around.

name: Manny Patino
text: Good pizza.

name: Janice Powell
text: Love the fresh ingredients and baking it at home!

name: Ashley Tuck
text: Awesome remind me of my childhood and the taste priceless
